<!-- ========== FAQ / SAFETY ========== -->
<section id="faq" style="background:var(--bg2)">
  <div class="wrap-sm">
    <div class="text-center">
      <div class="tag">FAQ &amp; Safety</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Questions? We get it.</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Especially the "is this safe?" ones. Here's everything.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What exactly am I downloading? <span class="arrow">&#9660;</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">A .zip file containing Markdown (.md) text files. No executables, no scripts, no binaries. Every file is human-readable — you can open them in any text editor and see exactly what's inside before doing anything with them. It's the safest kind of download there is.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How do I verify the files are safe? <span class="arrow">&#9660;</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">After downloading: 1) Right-click the .zip and check the file size (should be ~15-20 KB). 2) Unzip it and look at the folder structure — you should see only .md files. 3) Open any file in a text editor (Notepad, TextEdit, VS Code) and read it. If you see anything other than plain English text with some formatting, something is wrong. But you won't — because it's just Markdown.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does EVA have access to my data? <span class="arrow">&#9660;</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">EVA runs locally through your own AI tool (Claude, ChatGPT, etc.). Your data stays on your machine and goes only to the AI service you choose to use. We never see, store, or access your data after you download your files. The questionnaire data is used only to generate your files — it's not saved on our servers.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What AI tools does EVA work with? <span class="arrow">&#9660;</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">Any AI that accepts system prompts or file uploads. We recommend Claude Desktop (Projects) or ChatGPT (Custom GPTs). EVA also works with local LLMs like Ollama, LM Studio, or anything that reads text prompts. The files are platform-agnostic by design.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I customize EVA after download? <span class="arrow">&#9660;</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">Absolutely — that's the whole point. Every file is editable Markdown. Add new prompt templates, modify workflows, change your profile. You own the code. Fork it, extend it, make it yours. The structure is designed to be self-explanatory.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What does EVA NOT do? <span class="arrow">&#9660;</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">EVA does not write code, make marketing decisions, or make strategic business decisions for you. She's an operational assistant — she handles the admin, scheduling, communications, and follow-ups so you can focus on building. She surfaces information; you make the calls.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What if I need help after installing? <span class="arrow">&#9660;</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">You get free access to our support chat agent, which can answer questions from our knowledge base instantly. If you need deeper troubleshooting or custom help, our support agent will route you to a human or use reasoning capabilities (paid per use, billed via Stripe).</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is there a refund policy? <span class="arrow">&#9660;</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. If you're not satisfied within 14 days of purchase, we'll refund you in full — no questions asked. We want you to love EVA, not feel stuck.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

